Service Cloud

Set Up Service Contracts

Service contracts are agreements between you and your customers for a type of customer support. They can represent different kinds of customer support, such as subscriptions or service level agreements (SLAs).

To set up service contracts:

Manage Entitlements
Customize Application

Entitlements must be enabled in your org to set up service contracts.

From the object management settings for service contracts:

* Customize service contract fields.
* Customize service contract page layouts.
* Add customizations such as Status Icon field and Parent Service Contract field.
* Set field-level security on service contract fields.
* Set field history tracking on service contracts.
* Make the Service Contracts tab visible in Salesforce and any custom apps.
* Add the Service Contracts related list to account and contact page layouts.

SEE ALSO:

Entitlement Management Setup Checklist
Add Contract Line Items to Service Contracts
title: Setting Up Service Contracts in Salesforce
